ce:section.ce:para:
The surface elementary composition of MPC-POSS-PhE copolymers was further confirmed by XPS. As shown in Fig. 3
                           , the primary elements including carbon (C), oxygen (O), silicon (Si), nitrogen (N) phosphorus (P) and sulfur (S) were observed clearly by a survey XPS scan ranging from 0 to 1200eV. Furthermore, a survey with the high resolution XPS spectra of MPC-POSS-PhE showed six peaks at 285.2, 532.0, 102.8, 398.8, 132.9 and 163.8eV are attributed to elements of C, O, Si, N, P and S, respectively (Fig. 4
                           ). More importantly, the element mass percentage of C, O, Si, N, P and S was calculated based on the XPS spectra. The mass percentage of C, O, Si, N, P and S for MPC-POSS-PhE are 75.78%, 13.9%, 4.15%, 3.88%, 1.02% and 1.27%, respectively (Table S1). The XPS analysis provided complementary evidence for fabrication of MPC-POSS-PhE copolymers.
